&gt; The problem is that it only get evaluated when the Value changes, this won&#39;t work:


It is an expect result. The method `Clamp` will returns value clamped to the inclusive range of min and max.

```
template&lt;class T&gt;
T Clamp(T x, T min, T max)
{
    if (x &gt; max)
        return max;
    if (x &lt; min)
        return min;
    return x;
}
```

When you set `Value` as 0.7 ,and `MaxValue` as 0.8, because 0.7 is large than 0.05 and less then 0.8 ,so it will return itself (0.7). And the method propertyChanged will never been called .

When you set `Value` as 0.8 ,and `MaxValue` as 0.7, it will return 0.8. And the method propertyChanged will been called .

